	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hey Tebyn, after reading some of your posts on Mages, allow me to kindly ask you to stick to Druids cause you're not as well informed on Mages. <br><br>I give Velium weapons to my pets all the time in leiu of summoned because they proc at least once per fight. An extra 12 pts in a fight can really help sometimes. <br><br>My experience is to equip your pet best you should give rusty weapons, 1h weapons or summoned up till around 12th, from 12th to 16th give them Rusty 2h because otherwise you aren't helping their max damage.(Please note here... pets are not slowed by the delay on 2h weapons) AFTER 16 until about 24 you can arm if you choose, to help them achieve max damage more often when they hit. Once you hit 24, I would advise always arming them even if it is just with your 24th level summoned daggers, as they will dual wield if given the chance and weapons will help them score their max damage more often.<br><br>Again, I find it easy to keep pet armed with weapons from kills because at the higher levels No one really wants to tote around heavy weapons when they can be just as encumbered with coin that is worth more than said weapon.<br><br>(and be kind, arm your friendly enchanter and Necro pets too...)<br><br>Thayn<br>&nbsp;<br>Zaloren V'Shnev<br>Enchanter of Innoruuk<br>Master Jeweler<br>Journeyman Smith<br>Vazaelle</td></tr>
